description:
This is a 6 minute workout called 'Race on the Thames Warm-Up' from the channel Aisyah Rafaee.
The workout falls under Warm-up/Warm-up.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Meditative Grind and The Competitor vibe.
The The Meditative Grind vibe means Zone in, lock down, let repetition take over. This is especially good for Those who love a slow burn and rhythmic intensity. The The Competitor vibe means Gamified, leaderboard-driven, full-send energy. This is especially good for Those who need to chase a score or beat their own record..
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Ignite your leg drive and set your pace with Aisyah and Mike as you prepare to take on the Race on the Thames. 

Max rhythm: 32, Format: Interval ...
